### NEGATIVE / RULED-OUT
- Do not adopt a blanket new “reviewer” role: spec-kit already has @review plus sk-code-review with findings-first severity, security/correctness minimums, and read-only boundaries. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-code-review/SKILL.md:47-50] [SOURCE: .opencode/agents/review.md:29-31]
- Do not replace the Iron Law: Gem Team’s verification stack complements, but does not supersede, spec-kit’s existing hard verification before completion. [SOURCE: specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/gem-team-main/README.md:63-70] [SOURCE: AGENTS.md:13]
- Do not make universal TDD mandatory without scoping: current spec-kit supports multiple surfaces and already requires surface-appropriate tests/verification before claims. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-code/SKILL.md:187-193]

### OPEN QUESTIONS
- Should contract-first apply to all feature work, or only API/schema/integration boundaries?
- Should OWASP be a generic web/security checklist, or should mobile use MASVS-style checks like Gem Team’s reviewer references?
- Should critic-style review be a new agent mode, or a required @review pre-plan mode for high-complexity packets?

